{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":564,"text":"My job is to design, build and study\nrobots that communicate with people."},{"time":5231,"text":"But this story doesn't start with robotics\nat all, it starts with animation."},{"time":8874,"text":"When I first saw Pixar's \"Luxo Jr.,\""},{"time":11267,"text":"I was amazed by how much\nemotion they could put"},{"time":13997,"text":"into something as trivial as a desk lamp."},{"time":17477,"text":"I mean, look at them --\nat the end of this movie,"},{"time":19846,"text":"you actually feel something\nfor two pieces of furniture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":22649,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23954,"text":"And I said, I have\nto learn how to do this."},{"time":26006,"text":"So I made a really bad career decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28257,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29475,"text":"And that's what my mom\nwas like when I did it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31692,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":33857,"text":"I left a very cozy tech job in Israel\nat a nice software company"},{"time":37302,"text":"and I moved to New York\nto study animation."},{"time":39618,"text":"And there I lived"},{"time":40793,"text":"in a collapsing apartment building\nin Harlem with roommates."},{"time":43635,"text":"I'm not using this phrase\nmetaphorically --"},{"time":45683,"text":"the ceiling actually collapsed\none day in our living room."},{"time":48436,"text":"Whenever they did news stories\nabout building violations in New York,"},{"time":51702,"text":"they would put the report\nin front of our building,"},{"time":54142,"text":"as kind of, like, a backdrop\nto show how bad things are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56903,"text":"Anyway, during the day, I went to school"},{"time":58864,"text":"and at night I would sit and draw\nframe by frame of pencil animation."},{"time":62315,"text":"And I learned two surprising lessons."},{"time":64524,"text":"One of them was that\nwhen you want to arouse emotions,"},{"time":69038,"text":"it doesn't matter so much\nhow something looks;"},{"time":71237,"text":"it's all in the motion, in the timing\nof how the thing moves."},{"time":74816,"text":"And the second was something\none of our teachers told us."},{"time":78030,"text":"He actually did the weasel in \"Ice Age.\""},{"time":80662,"text":"And he said, \"As an animator,\nyou're not a director -- you're an actor.\""},{"time":84895,"text":"So, if you want to find\nthe right motion for a character,"},{"time":87942,"text":"don't think about it --\ngo use your body to find it."},{"time":90411,"text":"Stand in front of a mirror,\nact it out in front of a camera --"},{"time":93368,"text":"whatever you need -- and then\nput it back in your character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96696,"text":"A year later I found myself at MIT\nin the Robotic Life Group."},{"time":99932,"text":"It was one of the first groups\nresearching the relationships"},{"time":102814,"text":"between humans and robots."},{"time":104152,"text":"And I still had this dream\nto make an actual, physical Luxo Jr. lamp."},{"time":108132,"text":"But I found that robots didn't move\nat all in this engaging way"},{"time":111148,"text":"that I was used to\nfrom my animation studies."},{"time":113347,"text":"Instead, they were all --\nhow should I put it --"},{"time":115835,"text":"they were all kind of robotic."},{"time":117313,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":119211,"text":"And I thought, what if I took\nwhatever I learned in animation school,"},{"time":122971,"text":"and used that to design\nmy robotic desk lamp."},{"time":125598,"text":"So I went and designed frame by frame"},{"time":127667,"text":"to try to make this robot as graceful\nand engaging as possible."},{"time":132199,"text":"And here when you see the robot\ninteracting with me on a desktop --"},{"time":135932,"text":"and I'm actually redesigning the robot,"},{"time":137992,"text":"so, unbeknownst to itself,"},{"time":139820,"text":"it's kind of digging its own\ngrave by helping me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":142419,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":144449,"text":"I wanted it to be less of a mechanical\nstructure giving me light,"},{"time":147712,"text":"and more of a helpful,\nkind of quiet apprentice"},{"time":150754,"text":"that's always there when you need it\nand doesn't really interfere."},{"time":153947,"text":"And when, for example, I'm looking\nfor a battery that I can't find,"},{"time":157306,"text":"in a subtle way, it'll show me\nwhere the battery is."},{"time":161872,"text":"So you can see my confusion here."},{"time":164442,"text":"I'm not an actor."},{"time":168585,"text":"And I want you to notice\nhow the same mechanical structure"},{"time":171642,"text":"can, at one point,\njust by the way it moves,"},{"time":173753,"text":"seem gentle and caring\nand in the other case,"},{"time":175921,"text":"seem violent and confrontational."},{"time":178316,"text":"And it's the same structure,\njust the motion is different."},{"time":187419,"text":"Actor: \"You want to know something?\nWell, you want to know something?"},{"time":192015,"text":"He was already dead!"},{"time":193928,"text":"Just laying there, eyes glazed over!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":197854,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":198899,"text":"But, moving in a graceful way\nis just one building block"},{"time":201979,"text":"of this whole structure\ncalled human-robot interaction."},{"time":204598,"text":"I was, at the time, doing my PhD,\nI was working on human-robot teamwork,"},{"time":208075,"text":"teams of humans and robots\nworking together."},{"time":210161,"text":"I was studying the engineering,"},{"time":211820,"text":"the psychology,\nthe philosophy of teamwork,"},{"time":214376,"text":"and at the same time,"},{"time":215551,"text":"I found myself in my own kind\nof teamwork situation,"},{"time":218069,"text":"with a good friend of mine,\nwho's actually here."},{"time":220345,"text":"And in that situation,\nwe can easily imagine robots"},{"time":222773,"text":"in the near future being there with us."},{"time":224697,"text":"It was after a Passover Seder."},{"time":226411,"text":"We were folding up\na lot of folding chairs,"},{"time":228490,"text":"and I was amazed at how quickly\nwe found our own rhythm."},{"time":231172,"text":"Everybody did their own part,\nwe didn't have to divide our tasks."},{"time":234306,"text":"We didn't have to communicate\nverbally about this --"},{"time":236776,"text":"it all just happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237989,"text":"And I thought, humans and robots\ndon't look at all like this."},{"time":240893,"text":"When humans and robots interact,\nit's much more like a chess game:"},{"time":244048,"text":"the human does a thing, the robot\nanalyzes whatever the human did,"},{"time":247193,"text":"the robot decides what to do next,\nplans it and does it."},{"time":249860,"text":"Then the human waits,\nuntil it's their turn again."},{"time":252239,"text":"So it's much more like a chess game,\nand that makes sense,"},{"time":254994,"text":"because chess is great for mathematicians\nand computer scientists."},{"time":258129,"text":"It's all about information, analysis,\ndecision-making and planning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261581,"text":"But I wanted my robot\nto be less of a chess player,"},{"time":265335,"text":"and more like a doer"},{"time":267152,"text":"that just clicks and works together."},{"time":269177,"text":"So I made my second\nhorrible career choice:"},{"time":272570,"text":"I decided to study acting for a semester."},{"time":275147,"text":"I took off from the PhD,\nI went to acting classes."},{"time":278090,"text":"I actually participated in a play --"},{"time":280152,"text":"I hope thereâ€™s no video\nof that around still."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282478,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":283540,"text":"And I got every book\nI could find about acting,"},{"time":285858,"text":"including one from the 19th century\nthat I got from the library."},{"time":289011,"text":"And I was really amazed, because my name\nwas the second name on the list --"},{"time":292648,"text":"the previous name was in 1889."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294672,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":295711,"text":"And this book was\nkind of waiting for 100 years"},{"time":297984,"text":"to be rediscovered for robotics."},{"time":300340,"text":"And this book shows actors"},{"time":301940,"text":"how to move every muscle in the body"},{"time":304202,"text":"to match every kind of emotion\nthat they want to express."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306942,"text":"But the real revelation was\nwhen I learned about method acting."},{"time":309992,"text":"It became very popular\nin the 20th century."},{"time":312269,"text":"And method acting said"},{"time":313444,"text":"you don't have to plan\nevery muscle in your body;"},{"time":315768,"text":"instead, you have to use your body\nto find the right movement."},{"time":318737,"text":"You have to use your sense memory\nto reconstruct the emotions"},{"time":321641,"text":"and kind of think with your body\nto find the right expression --"},{"time":324703,"text":"improvise, play off your scene partner."},{"time":326602,"text":"And this came at the same time"},{"time":328071,"text":"as I was reading about this trend\nin cognitive psychology,"},{"time":331201,"text":"called embodied cognition,\nwhich also talks about the same ideas."},{"time":334477,"text":"We use our bodies to think;"},{"time":336016,"text":"we don't just think with our brains\nand use our bodies to move,"},{"time":338997,"text":"but our bodies feed back into our brain"},{"time":340939,"text":"to generate the way that we behave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":343128,"text":"And it was like a lightning bolt."},{"time":344748,"text":"I went back to my office,"},{"time":345986,"text":"I wrote this paper,\nwhich I never really published,"},{"time":348415,"text":"called \"Acting Lessons\nfor Artificial Intelligence.\""},{"time":350971,"text":"And I even took another month"},{"time":352376,"text":"to do what was then the first theater play"},{"time":354844,"text":"with a human and a robot acting together."},{"time":356821,"text":"That's what you saw\nbefore with the actors."},{"time":360564,"text":"And I thought:"},{"time":361739,"text":"How can we make an artificial\nintelligence model --"},{"time":364700,"text":"a computer, computational model --"},{"time":366707,"text":"that will model some of these\nideas of improvisation,"},{"time":369238,"text":"of taking risks, of taking chances,"},{"time":371092,"text":"even of making mistakes?"},{"time":372643,"text":"Maybe it can make for better\nrobotic teammates."},{"time":375280,"text":"So I worked for quite\na long time on these models"},{"time":377908,"text":"and I implemented them\non a number of robots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380327,"text":"Here you can see a very early example"},{"time":382652,"text":"with the robots trying to use\nthis embodied artificial intelligence"},{"time":386255,"text":"to try to match my movements\nas closely as possible."},{"time":388742,"text":"It's sort of like a game."},{"time":390530,"text":"Let's look at it."},{"time":395652,"text":"You can see when I psych\nit out, it gets fooled."},{"time":399698,"text":"And it's a little bit\nlike what you might see actors do"},{"time":402317,"text":"when they try to mirror each other"},{"time":403975,"text":"to find the right synchrony between them."},{"time":406364,"text":"And then, I did another experiment,"},{"time":408220,"text":"and I got people off the street\nto use the robotic desk lamp,"},{"time":412303,"text":"and try out this idea\nof embodied artificial intelligence."},{"time":415921,"text":"So, I actually used two kinds\nof brains for the same robot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420543,"text":"The robot is the same lamp that you saw,"},{"time":422519,"text":"and I put two brains in it."},{"time":423882,"text":"For one half of the people,"},{"time":425633,"text":"I put in a brain\nthat's kind of the traditional,"},{"time":428593,"text":"calculated robotic brain."},{"time":429846,"text":"It waits for its turn,\nit analyzes everything, it plans."},{"time":432510,"text":"Let's call it the calculated brain."},{"time":434216,"text":"The other got more the stage\nactor, risk-taker brain."},{"time":437487,"text":"Let's call it the adventurous brain."},{"time":439633,"text":"It sometimes acts without knowing\neverything it has to know."},{"time":442594,"text":"It sometimes makes mistakes\nand corrects them."},{"time":444910,"text":"And I had them do this very tedious task\nthat took almost 20 minutes,"},{"time":448852,"text":"and they had to work together,"},{"time":450352,"text":"somehow simulating, like, a factory job"},{"time":452929,"text":"of repetitively doing the same thing."},{"time":455445,"text":"What I found is that people\nactually loved the adventurous robot."},{"time":458800,"text":"They thought it was more intelligent,"},{"time":460601,"text":"more committed,\na better member of the team,"},{"time":462731,"text":"contributed to the success\nof the team more."},{"time":464820,"text":"They even called it \"he\" and \"she,\""},{"time":466552,"text":"whereas people with the calculated brain"},{"time":468697,"text":"called it \"it,\" and nobody\never called it \"he\" or \"she.\""},{"time":471876,"text":"When they talked about it after the task,\nwith the adventurous brain,"},{"time":475193,"text":"they said, \"By the end, we were good\nfriends and high-fived mentally.\""},{"time":479397,"text":"Whatever that means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480714,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":482644,"text":"Sounds painful."},{"time":484021,"text":"Whereas the people\nwith the calculated brain"},{"time":486783,"text":"said it was just like a lazy apprentice."},{"time":489165,"text":"It only did what it was supposed\nto do and nothing more,"},{"time":491934,"text":"which is almost what people\nexpect robots to do,"},{"time":494307,"text":"so I was surprised that people\nhad higher expectations of robots"},{"time":497886,"text":"than what anybody in robotics\nthought robots should be doing."},{"time":502027,"text":"And in a way, I thought,\nmaybe it's time --"},{"time":504066,"text":"just like method acting\nchanged the way people thought"},{"time":507052,"text":"about acting in the 19th century,"},{"time":508672,"text":"from going from the very calculated,\nplanned way of behaving,"},{"time":511773,"text":"to a more intuitive, risk-taking,\nembodied way of behaving --"},{"time":515295,"text":"maybe it's time for robots\nto have the same kind of revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519994,"text":"A few years later, I was at my next\nresearch job at Georgia Tech in Atlanta,"},{"time":523617,"text":"and I was working in a group\ndealing with robotic musicians."},{"time":526465,"text":"And I thought, music:\nthat's the perfect place"},{"time":528849,"text":"to look at teamwork, coordination,\ntiming, improvisation --"},{"time":533016,"text":"and we just got this robot\nplaying marimba."},{"time":535483,"text":"And the marimba, for everybody like me,"},{"time":537763,"text":"it was this huge, wooden xylophone."},{"time":540526,"text":"And when I was looking at this,"},{"time":542613,"text":"I looked at other works\nin human-robot improvisation --"},{"time":545635,"text":"yes, there are other works\nin human-robot improvisation --"},{"time":548406,"text":"and they were also a little bit\nlike a chess game."},{"time":550779,"text":"The human would play,"},{"time":551954,"text":"the robot analyzed what was played,"},{"time":554151,"text":"and would improvise their own part."},{"time":556254,"text":"So, this is what musicians called\na call-and-response interaction,"},{"time":559416,"text":"and it also fits very well\nrobots and artificial intelligence."},{"time":563187,"text":"But I thought, if I use the same ideas\nI used in the theater play"},{"time":566464,"text":"and in the teamwork studies,"},{"time":568232,"text":"maybe I can make the robots\njam together like a band."},{"time":571906,"text":"Everybody's riffing off each other,\nnobody is stopping for a moment."},{"time":576198,"text":"And so I tried to do the same\nthings, this time with music,"},{"time":579096,"text":"where the robot doesn't really know\nwhat it's about to play,"},{"time":581954,"text":"it just sort of moves its body\nand uses opportunities to play,"},{"time":584995,"text":"and does what my jazz teacher\nwhen I was 17 taught me."},{"time":587558,"text":"She said, when you improvise,"},{"time":588979,"text":"sometimes you don't know\nwhat you're doing, and you still do it."},{"time":592019,"text":"So I tried to make a robot that doesn't\nactually know what it's doing,"},{"time":595369,"text":"but is still doing it."},{"time":596614,"text":"So let's look at a few seconds\nfrom this performance,"},{"time":599149,"text":"where the robot listens\nto the human musician"},{"time":601300,"text":"and improvises."},{"time":602489,"text":"And then, look how the human\nmusician also responds"},{"time":605488,"text":"to what the robot is doing"},{"time":606785,"text":"and picking up from its behavior,"},{"time":609453,"text":"and at some point can even be surprised\nby what the robot came up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613433,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":655618,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":659134,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":664892,"text":"Being a musician\nis not just about making notes,"},{"time":667166,"text":"otherwise nobody\nwould ever go see a live show."},{"time":669538,"text":"Musicians also communicate\nwith their bodies,"},{"time":671684,"text":"with other band members,\nwith the audience,"},{"time":673725,"text":"they use their bodies\nto express the music."},{"time":675763,"text":"And I thought, we already have\na robot musician on stage,"},{"time":678484,"text":"why not make it be\na full-fledged musician?"},{"time":680820,"text":"And I started designing\na socially expressive head"},{"time":683518,"text":"for the robot."},{"time":684885,"text":"The head doesnâ€™t actually\ntouch the marimba,"},{"time":686979,"text":"it just expresses what the music is like."},{"time":688962,"text":"These are some napkin sketches\nfrom a bar in Atlanta"},{"time":691482,"text":"that was dangerously\nlocated exactly halfway"},{"time":694049,"text":"between my lab and my home."},{"time":695884,"text":"So I spent, I would say, on average,\nthree to four hours a day there."},{"time":699846,"text":"I think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701057,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702917,"text":"And I went back to my animation\ntools and tried to figure out"},{"time":705823,"text":"not just what a robotic\nmusician would look like,"},{"time":708217,"text":"but especially what a robotic\nmusician would move like,"},{"time":710866,"text":"to sort of show that it doesn't like\nwhat the other person is playing --"},{"time":714292,"text":"and maybe show whatever beat\nit's feeling at the moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718141,"text":"So we ended up actually getting the money\nto build this robot, which was nice."},{"time":722668,"text":"I'm going to show you now\nthe same kind of performance,"},{"time":725296,"text":"this time with a socially expressive head."},{"time":727360,"text":"And notice one thing --"},{"time":729184,"text":"how the robot is really showing us"},{"time":730879,"text":"the beat it's picking up from the human,"},{"time":732809,"text":"while also giving the human a sense\nthat the robot knows what it's doing."},{"time":736760,"text":"And also how it changes the way it moves"},{"time":738704,"text":"as soon as it starts its own solo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740680,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":744600,"text":"Now it's looking at me,\nshowing that it's listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747644,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769181,"text":"Now look at the final chord\nof the piece again."},{"time":772126,"text":"And this time the robot\ncommunicates with its body"},{"time":775067,"text":"when it's busy doing its own thing,"},{"time":777204,"text":"and when it's ready to coordinate\nthe final chord with me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782079,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":789783,"text":"(Music ending)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794103,"text":"(Final chord)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795128,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":800906,"text":"Thanks."},{"time":802085,"text":"I hope you see"},{"time":803690,"text":"how much this part of the body\nthat doesn't touch the instrument"},{"time":808110,"text":"actually helps\nwith the musical performance."},{"time":811160,"text":"And at some point -- we are in Atlanta,"},{"time":813193,"text":"so obviously some rapper\nwill come into our lab at some point --"},{"time":816467,"text":"and we had this rapper come in and do\na little jam with the robot."},{"time":821284,"text":"Here you can see the robot\nbasically responding to the beat."},{"time":825356,"text":"Notice two things:"},{"time":826531,"text":"one, how irresistible it is to join\nthe robot while it's moving its head."},{"time":830164,"text":"You kind of want to move\nyour own head when it does it."},{"time":832791,"text":"And second, even though the rapper\nis really focused on his iPhone,"},{"time":836401,"text":"as soon as the robot turns\nto him, he turns back."},{"time":839535,"text":"So even though it's just\nin the periphery of his vision,"},{"time":842195,"text":"in the corner of his eye,\nit's very powerful."},{"time":844339,"text":"And the reason is that we can't ignore"},{"time":846197,"text":"physical things moving in our environment."},{"time":848245,"text":"We are wired for that."},{"time":849439,"text":"So if you have a problem --"},{"time":851107,"text":"maybe your partner is looking\nat their iPhone or smartphone too much --"},{"time":855806,"text":"you might want to have a robot\nthere to get their attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858664,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":859689,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":874113,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":878138,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":885633,"text":"Just to introduce the last robot\nthat we've worked on,"},{"time":889491,"text":"it came out of something\nsurprising that we found:"},{"time":891865,"text":"Some point people didn't care\nabout the robot being intelligent,"},{"time":895047,"text":"able to improvise and listen,"},{"time":896473,"text":"and do all these embodied intelligence\nthings that I spent years developing."},{"time":900903,"text":"They really liked that the robot\nwas enjoying the music."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903608,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904633,"text":"And they didn't say the robot\nwas moving to the music,"},{"time":907202,"text":"they said \"enjoying\" the music."},{"time":908714,"text":"And we thought,\nwhy don't we take this idea,"},{"time":910864,"text":"and I designed a new piece of furniture."},{"time":913629,"text":"This time it wasn't a desk lamp,\nit was a speaker dock,"},{"time":916225,"text":"one of those things\nyou plug your smartphone in."},{"time":918889,"text":"And I thought,"},{"time":920063,"text":"what would happen if your speaker dock\ndidn't just play the music for you,"},{"time":923587,"text":"but would actually enjoy it, too?"},{"time":925657,"text":"And so again, here are some\nanimation tests from an early stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929842,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931835,"text":"And this is what the final\nproduct looked like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946247,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":966848,"text":"(Music ends)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":969461,"text":"So, a lot of bobbing heads."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972105,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":975740,"text":"A lot of bobbing heads in the audience,"},{"time":977654,"text":"so we can still see\nrobots influence people."},{"time":980386,"text":"And it's not just fun and games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983195,"text":"I think one of the reasons I care so much"},{"time":985420,"text":"about robots that use\ntheir body to communicate"},{"time":987677,"text":"and use their body to move is --"},{"time":989407,"text":"I'm going to let you in on a little\nsecret we roboticists are hiding --"},{"time":992821,"text":"is that every one of you\nis going to be living with a robot"},{"time":995638,"text":"at some point in your life."},{"time":997254,"text":"Somewhere in your future,\nthere will be a robot in your life."},{"time":1000211,"text":"If not in yours, your children's lives."},{"time":1002103,"text":"And I want these robots to be more fluent,\nmore engaging, more graceful"},{"time":1007117,"text":"than currently they seem to be."},{"time":1008870,"text":"And for that I think maybe robots\nneed to be less like chess players"},{"time":1012181,"text":"and more like stage actors\nand more like musicians."},{"time":1014846,"text":"Maybe they should be able\nto take chances and improvise."},{"time":1017683,"text":"Maybe they should be able\nto anticipate what you're about to do."},{"time":1020731,"text":"Maybe they even need to be able\nto make mistakes and correct them,"},{"time":1024103,"text":"because in the end, we are human."},{"time":1026015,"text":"And maybe as humans,\nrobots that are a little less than perfect"},{"time":1029593,"text":"are just perfect for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031348,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1032531,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}